value:
Provenance: ms. inscr. on front free e.p. of vol.: 'T. Kerrich M.C.C. 1804'.
Binding: panelled calf & sprinkled calf, blind stamped; spine blind stamped, raised bands, g. lettering; rebacked.

De varietate figurarum et flexuris partium ac gestib. imaginum.
De symmetria partium in rectis formis hu[m]anorum corporum
With: Elementa geometrica / Albrecht Dürer. Parisiis: Christiani Wecheli, 1535, & 2 others.
Volume 2 (books 3-4) has title: Clariss. pictoris et geometra[e] Alberti Dureri De varietate figurarum et flexuris partium ac gestib. imaginum libro duo : qui priorib. de symmetria quondam editis : nunc primum in latinum conuersi accesserunt ...
Translation by Joachim Camerarius of books 1 and 2 of Vier buc̈her von menschlicher Proportion.
Imprint from colophon of volume 1, which reads: "Norimbergae excubatur opus aestate anni A Christo seruatore genito MDXXII ..."
Colophon of volume 2: Finitum opus anno a salutifero partu 1534, 9 cal. Decemb. Impensis viduae Durerianae, per Hieronymum Formschneyder Norinbergae.
Translated by Joachim Camerarius, the elder (preface signed "Jo. Ca.").
Dürer's initials "A D" in large letters on the title page.
References: Adams D1044. Anatomy, Artistic Early works to 1800. Proportion (Anthropometry) Early works to 1800. Body size Early works to 1800.
